properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 6 at 2:08PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds will likely increase to 30 to 40 mph with
gusts to 50 mph. A few wind gusts will reach 60 mph along Outer
Drive just south of Casper, as well as along some of the higher
ridges.

* WHERE...Along the Highway 287 corridor from Beaver Rim to
Sweetwater Station and Jeffrey City, and along the Highway 220
corridor from Alcova to Casper.

* WHEN...Tuesday with the strongest wind likely to occur from 11
AM to 6 PM.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Anyone traveling along Highway 20/26, 220,
287 and Interstate 25 on Tuesday should anticipate sudden
strong cross winds.

NWSheadline: Winds expected to increase once again from Jeffrey City to Casper on Tuesday
